{"Title": "New SMARCA2 mutation in a patient with Nicolaides\u2013Baraitser syndrome and myoclonic astatic epilepsy", "Year": 2017, "Source": "Am. J. Med. Genet. Part A", "Volume": "173", "Issue": 1, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 195, "PageEnd": 199, "CitedBy": 9, "DOI": "10.1002/ajmg.a.37935", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84995693998&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2016 The Authors. American Journal of Medical Genetics Part A published by Wiley Periodicals, Inc.We report a de novo SMARCA2 missense mutation discovered on exome sequencing in a patient with myoclonic astatic epilepsy, leading to reassessment and identification of Nicolaides\u2013Baraitser syndrome. This de novo SMARCA2 missense mutation c.3721C>G, p.Gln1241Glu is the only reported mutation on exon 26 outside the ATPase domain of SMARCA2 to be associated with Nicolaides\u2013Baraitser syndrome and adds to chromatin remodeling as a pathway for epileptogenesis. \u00a9 2016 The Authors. American Journal of Medical Genetics Part A published by Wiley Periodicals, Inc.", "AuthorKeywords": ["myoclonic astatic epilepsy", "Nicolaides\u2013Baraitser syndrome", "SMARCA2"], "IndexKeywords": ["Alleles", "Comparative Genomic Hybridization", "DNA Mutational Analysis", "Electroencephalography", "Epilepsies, Myoclonic", "Exons", "Facies", "Female", "Foot Deformities, Congenital", "Genotype", "Humans", "Hypotrichosis", "Infant", "Intellectual Disability", "Magnetic Resonance Imaging", "Mutation", "Phenotype", "Transcription Factors"], "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 1, "EID": "2-s2.0-84995693998", "SubjectAreas": [["Genetics", "BIOC", "1311"], ["Genetics (clinical)", "MEDI", "2716"]], "AuthorData": {"55303905800": {"Name": "Tang S.", "AuthorID": "55303905800", "AffiliationID": "60109217", "AffiliationName": "King's Health Partners"}, "7201701101": {"Name": "Simpson M.A.", "AuthorID": "7201701101", "AffiliationID": "60011520", "AffiliationN